<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-8865] Specifying initial heap size results in an error</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-8865</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On Windows, setting initial heap size greater than 128MB without setting maximum heap size, e.g. JAVA_OPTS=-Xms1G, results in the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Error occurred during initialization of VM&lt;br/&gt;
Initial heap size set to a larger value than the maximum heap size&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This works fine on Linux. And it is a valid&#160;JVM parameter, since JVM will set its maximum heap to be the greater of its default value and initial heap size.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Windows 10, OpenJDK 11.0.1</environment>
