                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16671027" author="paulk" created="Thu, 1 Nov 2018 02:09:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is it a Groovy or Java issue? Do you have a stacktrace?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16672061" author="rsmirnov" created="Thu, 1 Nov 2018 19:20:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem is with the way Groovy initializes JVM. There is no stacktrace, the error is the only output.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16672184" author="paulk" created="Thu, 1 Nov 2018 20:56:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Okay, understood. Looks like we hard code a value for -Xmx:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/groovy/blob/master/src/bin/startGroovy.bat#L262&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/groovy/blob/master/src/bin/startGroovy.bat#L262&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Obviously we should not do that if a user supplies their own -Xmx and/or the value should be at least as big as any -Xms setting.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16672508" author="paulk" created="Fri, 2 Nov 2018 02:40:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have removed our explicit setting. Reading up on the default value for that setting on current JVMs, I suspect it will be set to a higher value on most folks systems.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
